sql:
SELECT param_name, description
FROM well_parameters
WHERE unit = 'Ratio';

SELECT AVG(swat_value) AS average_swat_value
FROM swat
WHERE source = 'sensor' AND date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';

SELECT well_id, date, oil_rate
FROM production_data
WHERE oil_rate > 500;

SELECT w.well_name, pd.oil_rate, pd.gas_rate, pd.water_rate
FROM wells w
INNER JOIN production_data pd ON w.well_id = pd.well_id;

external_knowledge:
- Consistently produced: More than one entry in production_data, indicating production on multiple dates; 
- Identities: Refers to well_id and well_name; 
- Active years: Refers to the earliest and latest dates of production.

sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM wells) AS TotalWells,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM production_data) AS TotalProductionData;

SELECT swat_value
FROM swat
WHERE well_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Well identities refer to unique identifiers assigned to each well; 
Well names are the given names of the wells; 
Locations refer to the fields where the wells are situated; 
Type descriptions refer to the names of the well types, which could be, for example, oil, gas, or water wells.
